Results.ReviewText: I've drank Nescafé Gold Blend for a number of years. For an instant coffee it has a really good flavour, and doesn't suffer from the bitterness that other instant coffees often have. It's the only instant coffee I'd drink.
Results.Title: Smooth compared to other instant coffees

Results.ReviewText: Bought 4 jars, to make sure I got new packaging, got home and opened the jar to smell that great coffee aroma, wow! Better than ever, got pride of place by my kettle and my mug tree. Great cold as a refreshing pick me up!
Results.Title: Great Update, Contents Fab!

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe gold blend is pure gold. A delicious aroma and taste to set you up for the day ahead. Nescafe gold blend has a smooth rich taste to be enjoyed anywhere, anytime. This is the caffeine fix that beats all the others.
Results.Title: Coffee at its finest

Results.ReviewText: This is surely the very best quality of coffee around which is turned into the Gold Blend Instant Coffee.  The taste is what you would expect from the Gold standard of coffee and together its sure is good value for money.
Results.Title: A real Gold star for a Coffee drinker

Results.ReviewText:
I have bought Nescafe products for years, so delicious especially topped up with a little cream with a cinnamon biscuit makes my day.

Once you have drank Nescafe Gold Blens Rich and Smooth you won't want anything else.
Results.Title: Simply Divine Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I just love Necafe always have but love the flavour of the Nescafe Gold, i can tell the difference you cannot match the taste of Necafe you cannot substitute it with any other coffee as my mam used to try and do with me!
Results.Title: Lovely Coffee!!!

Results.ReviewText: My wife and I have used Gold Blend for a long time and consider it to be the best available.  It does not have the bitter taste of many other coffee's and a smoothness so is a delight to drink, both with or without milk.
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold Blend Instant

ClientResponses.Response: That's not good to hear, thank you for letting us know though. You're correct, during the recent recipe change, micro ground coffee was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: How disappointing.  It leaves a residue at the bottom of your cup which I would imagine is designed to give it a real coffee feel, the taste is the same and is the same high quality but it puts me off.  Sorry Gold Blend.
Results.Title: Oh Dear!

Results.ReviewText: Great Quality as always. Does leave a residue at the bottom of the cup like when you make a filtered coffee.  Guess this is because it contains a good quantity of ground coffee. Good rounded flavour. My always buy brand.
Results.Title: Coffee Addict!

Results.ReviewText:
Why has Gold Blend started having brown scum and grits in the bottom of the cup. We have been drinking Gold Blend for years now you have spoilt it.

Also why have the refill packs been reduced from 300 to 275 grammes.
Results.Title: Have you added the floor sweepings to Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: Whenever I need the taste of freshly made coffee, without the hassle of grinding, percolating etc., I always use Gold Blend. The natural taste and bitterness of real coffee is instantly available to me and so enjoyable.
Results.Title: Still the Best!

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thank you very much for leaving your review! Although it's disappointing to hear you're not a fan, we really appreciate your feedback!

Results.ReviewText: I’ve used gold blend for 30 or more years and loved it, the new one is bitter and leaves a horrible after taste and bits in the bottom of your cup . Two spoons of coffee black and nasty  please please bring the old back
Results.Title: Bring the old one back

Results.ReviewText: I love my gold blend coffee.. I love opening  a new jar and sniff the coffee.. I just think of summer mornings sitting on a balcony in spain enjoying my coffee and the summer sunshine.. what more could you want.. bliss!
Results.Title: gold blend

Results.ReviewText:
We have been using  Gold Blend for  years ... friends and family pop in for  "  a  proper  cup of coffee"  ..  they  say !
BIG BUT .....  What is going on, with all the  grains in the bottom of our cups ?.
Not happy !
Results.Title: FULL  FLAVOUR FAVORITE !

Results.ReviewText: I always usually buy the Nescafé original but my husband picked the gold up in error - we haven’t looked back since - it is a really enjoyable coffee to drink with no unpleasant bitterness that some other coffees have .
Results.Title: Tastes delicious

Results.ReviewText: I've been buying this coffee since my student days. Although coffee drinking habits have changed substantially since my college days in the '80s, this is still my "go to" coffee. Its flavour is deep, intense but smooth.
Results.Title: Good Tasting Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I decided to have a change in my coffee. Not sure what I was looking for but decided to try this blend. Loved it from the word "go"! Great flavour and wonderfully smooth. I love sitting down and drinking my coffee now.
Results.Title: Wonderfully smooth

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for leaving your review! We really value everyone's comments regarding the changes we've made & will be passing your feedback to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I loved gold blend and it has been my favourite for many years. However, noticed the new gold blend does not match the old one in terms of quality or taste. It is weaker and rather bland. Please bring back the old one.
Results.Title: Not good.

Results.ReviewText: Just love this coffee - smooth and yet strong without any bitterness.  Has been our favourite for many years.  Have tried the other varieties but still come back to this particular one.  Wouldn't swap it for the world.
Results.Title: Favourite all time coffee

Results.ReviewText: This is a product that gives luxury, for a reasonable price. The taste is superb, and goes well with cream. The coffee is well-balanced, and the blend gives all the stimulating taste of coffee, while remaining smooth.
Results.Title: Smooth and luxurious.

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it saddens us to hear how unhappy you are with the changes we've made but thanks for taking the time & leaving your feedback with us.

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Gold Blend for years and can't believe you have changed it. The black sludge at the bottom is horrible and it tastes bitter too. I'm trying to find a replacement as love my coffee but i'm so disappointed.
Results.Title: Why have you changed Gold blend

Results.ReviewText:
I have been drinking this coffee for years and, although it seems to have altered slightly recently, I still find it to be the best one I have tasted. 
It has a lovely rich flavour and just the right strength for me.
Results.Title: Lovely Rich Roast

Results.ReviewText:
The new jar looks like most of the own brands jars - bring back the one with the waist
Also don't like the powdery stuff at the bottom of the cup - you never used to get that.  Fortunately the taste is still as good!
Results.Title: Don't like new jar and other bits

Results.ReviewText: This is our little piece of luxury. We have tried other coffees but they do not taste as good as Gold Blend. Good isn't cheap and cheap isn't good. It is worth spending that little bit more on, you will not regret it.
Results.Title: Best of them all!

Results.ReviewText: I have had gold blend for years and was happy with the taste.When I saw the new style jars I thought here we go ,changing something again I'm not going to like this. Well I do.its great ,Sooooo well done !!!!!!!!!!!!
Results.Title: I didn't think it was going to be good.

Results.ReviewText: Best coffee around it's the only one I use I have a little glass jar I keep in my bag where ever I go so I can enjoy my coffee anywhere even if I go to friends houses and they don't stock it I bring my little jar out
Results.Title: Super coffee

Results.ReviewText:
Gold Blend seems to have less flavour than before, and there has been a noticeable increase in the amount of dusty muck left at the bottom of the cup.
Definitely a step backward; I may start looking at other brands.
Results.Title: Too much dust

Results.ReviewText:
This is a great instant coffee. It has a smooth taste and hits the spot. You get a coffee house taste in a conveniently instant hit.
If I'm out to buy coffee I preferably buy it all the time. Well done nescafe......
Results.Title: Coffee of choice

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for taking the time & leaving your thoughts with us.

Results.ReviewText: I wish to add my comment to others who can't drink the new Nescafé Gold Blend coffee.  I am saddened that you have changed the recipe for my favourite instant coffee, and am sincerely hoping you will change it back.
Results.Title: Poor taste - can't drink it now.

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for the feedback. We will be making a note of your comments.

Results.ReviewText: as many as the previous reviews I wholeheartedly agree with all there reviews. I am now on the hunt for a new coffee, has anyone found one!!!  Nescafe get your act together and bring the aroma and blend back please.
Results.Title: Ruined
